ven dependencies and bundles the platform JNI libraries. Meaningful tests should preserve the existing Java module opens because Conscrypt reflects into JDK internals on modern JDKs.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Keep the existing JVM/native-image test setup that adds opens for java.base/java.lang, java.base/java.net, and java.base/sun.nio.ch to ALL-UNNAMED. Tests should explicitly initialize/use the Conscrypt provider, e.g. Conscrypt.checkAvailability(), Conscrypt.newProvider(), and SSLContext/Cipher/Signature APIs with that provider, rather than relying on Conscrypt being installed globally.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Conscrypt extracts and loads a bundled JNI library from META-INF/native; if the runtime temp directory is mounted noexec, tests may need -Dorg.conscrypt.native.workdir=<writable-executable-dir>, but this is not normally required on the Gradle/CI environment.\",\n    \"The uber artifact only bundles native libraries for its published OpenJDK platforms; coverage remains platform-sensitive, especially under Native Image.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_055c50ad5b30d549016a42b91985c081968119739a5fded882\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6520, "output": 781, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48773, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782757647313, "responseId": "resp_055c50ad5b30d549016a42b90fd6a48196b2e6c40fa7477399"}}
